          "data": {
            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><h2 id=\"great-job\">\ud83c\udf89 Great Job!</h2>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">You've learned data wrangling with Polars! You now know how to:</span>\n<ul>\n<li>\u2705 Load CSV, JSON, and Parquet files</li>\n<li>\u2705 Explore and understand your data</li>\n<li>\u2705 Filter and select data</li>\n<li>\u2705 Create new calculated columns</li>\n<li>\u2705 Handle missing values</li>\n<li>\u2705 Group and aggregate data</li>\n<li>\u2705 Work with dates</li>\n<li>\u2705 Join multiple datasets</li>\n<li>\u2705 Chain operations for complex analysis</li>\n</ul>\n<span class=\"paragraph\"><strong>Next step:</strong> Open <code>03_plotting.py</code> to learn data visualization!</span></span>"
